The National Education, Health and Allied Workers Union says the increasing number of health workers infected with COVID-19 is concerning. It's Secretary Zola Saphetha says this proves that adequate personal protective equipment is absent. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Education, Health and Allied Workers Union (Nehawu) said the increasing number of health workers infected with COVID-19 is concerning. Secretary Zola Saphetha said this proves that adequate personal protective equipment is absent. READ: Nehawu fights for protective equipment "You have a national infection of 8,000 plus and out of it you have health workers, people who have to save lives, of that number 511 being infected," said Saphetha. "We are not happy with the infection of the health workers because those are the people who want to save lives." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.